data.description: We have the perfect home for YOU at 119 Poinsett Avenue! This adorable bungalow is tucked into the cozy town of Pickens, South Carolina, which is located at the base of the Blue Ridge mountains - you'll see why the town's motto is "Where the Mountains Begin!" This single story home was originally built in the 1920's, which means you'll find hardwood floors under the carpet of this home. The living room already showcases these beautiful floors and leads into the large kitchen with eating area. There are two, large bedrooms as well a bathroom that has been updated since the home's original construction. Windows were also updated. The large laundry room has ideal functionality and provides additional storage. It's also the access point to your privately fenced backyard! The idyllic deck is nestled among the mature landscaping and features a pergola with canopy (offered "as is") and leads you to the detached workshop! Located 30 minutes from Clemson and 30 minutes from Greenville, you'll enjoy a more rural lifestyle while still having convenient access to big city fun! Like to hike and kayak? You're a 15 minute drive from Table Rock State Park! Come experience a special lifestyle. Ask about a $12,500 closing cost assistance loan program for First Time Home Buyers!
